    "updated_at": "2018-02-14T00:10:42Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@parmeshthee Try using the subjectAltName instead of CN - it worked for me with an IP address (in Python, but the code that verifies the domain is in the C++ core regardless).\r\n\r\nFor reference, see https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/core/tsi/ssl_transport_security.cc, function `tsi_ssl_peer_matches_name()`. It explains step by step how the domain name is verified."
